Excerpt: Jay Chou (traditional Chinese: simplified Chinese: pinyin: Zh u Jielun; Wade-Giles: Chou Chieh-lun; Pe h- e-j: Chiu Kia t-lun; born 18 January 1979) is a Taiwanese musician, singer-songwriter, music and film producer, actor and director who has won the World Music Award four times. He is well-known for composing all his own songs and songs for other singers. In 1998 he was discovered in a talent contest where he displayed his piano and song-writing skills.
